data.name: label4.Text
data.value: The accident occurred at approximately 3:00 PM on February 14, 2024, at the intersection of Main Street and Elm Avenue. Vehicle A, traveling eastbound on Main Street, failed to stop at the stop sign and collided with vehicle B, which was proceeding southbound on Elm Avenue. The collision resulted in significant damage to the front end of vehicle A and the right side of vehicle B. Weather conditions at the time of the accident were clear, and the road surface was dry. Both drivers exchanged contact and insurance information at the scene. Police were called to the scene, and a report was filed documenting the details of the accident. Witnesses confirmed that vehicle A did not come to a complete stop at the stop sign before entering the intersection. Both drivers reported no injuries at the time of the accident.
